{
  "stem": "22979.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Slovakia became, you know, when Hitler took the Sudeten-- Slovakia became an independent state, Nazi-oriented, with the head of the state a Catholic priest, Dr.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Josef Tico.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "T-I-C-O-- Tico, not Tito.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, the propaganda, the loudspeakers, and you know, defacing the Jewish stores with Stars of David-- in the center of the main street where our house was, was big letters, you know, with white paint-- Jews and Gypsies, the same-- you deserve-- you know, I'm just translating from Slovak, which was in rhyme-- you deserve a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never heard about concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't-- didn't know what's the meaning of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But suddenly, our lives turned upside down.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Since we lived on the main street, and our house was there, Jews were not allowed to live on the main street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were relocated to the back of the city-- still not a ghetto-- where, with other families, we shared a little place, a house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then it was curfew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We could go out only a few hours a day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Since my father-- you know, he-- his business went bankrupt already in '36.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at this time, he was already a Hebrew teacher-- like you say in Hebrew, [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he didn't earn too much money, didn't have too much savings.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my brothers-- and because I have to come back still with my brothers-- they went and did farm work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And for return, they brought home some food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we lived with this, you know, quite a while-- and the slogans, and the propaganda, and the loud speakers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the worst thing was my good friends with whom I went to school and with whom we share-- I shared everything.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I am talking personally, my experience-- they were not my friends anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
